    "The results are summarized in Tables 2 and 3.",
    "For all experiments in this section, we ran each setting five times with different random seeds and reported the average results.",
    "The number of nonsensical concepts for TIP was set to 2, and prompts in all methods were evaluated in a zero-shot setting.Table 2 presents the performance across different models and methods on the ComVE dataset.",
    "In this table, the \"knowledge generator\" refers to the LLMs used for knowledge grounding, while the \"explanation generator\" represents the LLMs employed for generating the final explanations.",
    "The \"Method\" column indicates the different methods applied for this task."
